      "patchset_number": 1,
      "line": 13,
      "message": "Ansible modules are declarative, if 'systemd' module run with 'state: stopped' exited with success then the result is 'stopped', no need to perform this kind of hacks IMO. And if for some reason this is the case however then i think we need some proper check to ensure docker stopped, not some random sleep.",
